title.narrative: Fiscal Reform and Public Financial Management project (FRPFM)

description.narrative: The Jordan Fiscal Reform and Public Financial Management project (FRPFM) contributes to the USAID Mission Goal of Improved Prosperity, Accountability, and Equality for a Stable Democratic Jordan, specifically to improve Fiscal Stability and Public Financial Management. FRPFM focuses on four components to accomplish these objectives: 1. Revenue performance through improved tax policy and administration; 2. Budget efficiency and transparency; 3. Fiscal sustainability through structural reforms; and 4. Exit strategy.
